  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a node operator, I want peer counts to be maintained within bounds so that I can continue to particpate in the network. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Peer counts are maintained above `--p2p-peer-lower-bound`\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nPeer counts generally drop over time. When they drop below `--p2p-peer-lower-bound` I expect more peers to be added.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\nOver long runs on testnets I observe that peer counts continue to drop irrespective of `--p2p-peer-lower-bound`.\r\n\r\nFor example, running on Altona, over 24 hours my peer count has declined steadily from 29 to 16. `--p2p-peer-lower-bound` is at the default value of 20, so new peers should have been sought and added by now.\r\n\r\n**Frequency:**\r\nSeems consistent, It may explain #2200 and #2102\r\n",
